            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-07-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-10-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="519" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d519">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Protocol of Provisional Application of the General Agreement on Tariffs and
                    Trade was signed by Winthrop Brown for the United States at Geneva on October
                    30, 1947; the agreement was to take effect on January 1, 1948. The General
                    Agreement on Tariffs and Trade is printed as 61 Stat, (parts 5 and 6). For
                    documentation regarding the continuing effort to create an international trade
                    organization and the Havana Conference, see <ref target="frus1948v01p1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1948, volume I</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
